      "id": "BTqCGN30Zuo",
      "user": "Charlie",
      "text": "When you create a comment, you give it a temporary ID (like Date.now()). But the server responds with a real database ID. If a user tries to reply to that comment before the server responds, the parentId will point to the \"fake\" ID, and the reply will \"break\" or vanish when the page refreshes.",
      "parentId": null,
      "reactions": {
        "thumbsUp": 0,
        "heart": 0,
        "laugh": 0
      },
      "createdAt": "2026-03-25T18:50:48.910Z"
