    {
      "id": "aLFSrkZYC0U",
      "user": "Taylor",
      "text": "First, we need to be able to identify each comment. We'll use a dynamic ref on the CommentItem.",
      "parentId": null,
      "reactions": {
        "thumbsUp": 0,
        "heart": 0,
        "laugh": 0
      },
      "createdAt": "2026-03-25T19:39:35.964Z"
    },
    {
      "id": "Hw41Y2iiTjU",
      "user": "Alex",
      "text": "To handle scrolling to a newly created comment, we need a way to \"find\" the new element in the DOM after the list re-renders. Since you're using TanStack Query, the data fetch is asynchronous, so we have to wait for the data to actually arrive and Vue to finish its \"tick.\"",
      "parentId": null,
      "reactions": {
        "thumbsUp": 0,
        "heart": 0,
        "laugh": 0
      },
      "createdAt": "2026-03-25T19:39:58.066Z"
    },
    {
      "id": "eGBWNfzos7A",
      "user": "Charlie",
      "text": "Everything is looking strictly professional now. Would you like to add a \"Character Counter\" that turns red when the user gets close to a 500-character limit?",
      "parentId": null,
      "reactions": {
        "thumbsUp": 0,
        "heart": 0,
        "laugh": 0
      },
      "createdAt": "2026-03-25T19:40:26.799Z"
    },
    {
      "id": "1Qa1zE6u8Hs",
      "user": "Taylor",
      "text": "Since you are using field-sizing: content (a very modern and cool CSS property!), the textarea might \"flicker\" in height for a split second when you press Enter if you don't use .prevent. Using keydown keeps the height stable during submission.",
      "parentId": null,
      "reactions": {
        "thumbsUp": 0,
        "heart": 3,
