    {
      "id": "pJ7nUNFyNFI",
      "user": "isabellad",
      "text": "There are many SASS/SCSS variables @emmaj  that can be customized across the entire Vuetify framework. You can browse all the variables using the tool below:\n\n",
      "parentId": null,
      "reactions": {
        "thumbsUp": 0,
        "heart": 0,
        "laugh": 0
      },
      "createdAt": "2026-03-26T15:26:44.470Z",
      "editedAt": "2026-03-26T15:49:30.129Z"
    },
    {
      "id": "v5XwR9UbnRg",
      "user": "averyp",
      "text": "Utility classes are a powerful feature of Vuetify, but they can also be unnecessary for some projects. You can either disable them all at once or selecively keeping only what you plan to use. To disable all utility classes, set the entire $utilities variable to false:\n\n",
      "parentId": null,
      "reactions": {
        "thumbsUp": 0,
        "heart": 0,
        "laugh": 0
      },
      "createdAt": "2026-03-26T15:26:53.355Z",
      "editedAt": "2026-03-26T15:49:00.549Z"
    },
    {
      "id": "wKDPFTDy-9w",
      "user": "averyp",
      "text": "replay @liamg @miar @abigailr ",
      "parentId": "VBSL-NVje_A",
      "reactions": {
        "thumbsUp": 0,
        "heart": 0,
        "laugh": 0
      },
      "createdAt": "2026-03-26T15:40:27.966Z"
    },
    {
      "id": "8Je1ihtSmew",
      "user": "madisonc",
      "text": "Vuetify works out of the box @mateon  without any additional compilers needing to be installed but does support advanced use-cases such as modifying the underlying variables of the framework. Vite provides built-in support for sass, less and stylus files without the need to install Vite-specific plugins for them; just the corresponding pre-processor itself.\n\n",
      "parentId": null,
      "reactions": {
        "thumbsUp": 0,
        "heart": 1,
        "laugh": 0
      },
      "createdAt": "2026-03-26T16:07:49.693Z"
    },
    {
      "id": "HE55NG8tQEA",
      "user": "madisonc",
      "text": "configFile will be resolved relative to the project root, and loaded before each of vuetify’s stylesheets. Next, create a settings.scss file in your src/styles directory:\n\n",
      "parentId": "v5XwR9UbnRg",
      "reactions": {
        "thumbsUp": 0,
        "heart": 0,
        "laugh": 0
      },
      "createdAt": "2026-03-26T16:08:11.257Z"
    },
